<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-04-18T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-04-18T13:00:00-05:00" n="897" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d897">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00112 European War 1939/10581:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Ankara</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-04-18T20:00:00+02:00">April
                                        18, 1944—8 p.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received 9:40 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>699. Department’s 325, April 14.<note n="24" xml:id="d897fn24">See
                                    last sentence of footnote 18, <ref target="#pg_825">p.
                                    825</ref>.</note> I have kept the Russian Ambassador informed
                                concerning our note to the Turk Government with respect to trade
                                between Turkey and the Axis and immediately following my talk with
                                the Minister for Foreign Affairs (see my 678, April 15, 6 p.m.)
                                furnished Vinogradov with a copy of our note.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Steinhardt</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>